snippet.textDisplay:
As much as I want AMD to beat Nvdia right now....
What gap? It's not like 1060 and 1070 went on smoke. There isn't really a gap just because 2060 and below doesn't exist yet.
What we REALLY need are GTX 2080Ti equivalents, something with the performance of 2080Ti w/o the RTX features and tax which most of us don't care about.
But as much as I am rooting for AMD to get there.... it's almost as unlikely as Nvidia providing actual GTX 2080Ti as an option.
